{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e18a59ad-d3e0-4d8b-af22-bdc4687eafd2","content":"Here's what to change:\n\n1. **Update NUnit3TestAdapter** to **4.6.0+** (you're already there ✅).\n\n2. **Add the MTP adapter package**:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"NUnit.Extension.MicrosoftTestingPlatformSupport\" Version=\"4.*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Remove** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` — it's the VSTest entry-point and is no longer needed.\n\n4. **Enable MTP** in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n5. **Run tests** with the same command:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n\n**Key differences after migration:**\n- Each test project becomes its own executable (no `vstest.console` host).\n- `--` CLI args change; e.g. `--filter` becomes `--treenode-filter` when running the exe directly, but `dotnet test --filter` still works.\n- `.runsettings` files are still supported.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"52f206f2-1906-4422-99f7-2f9bb00b0eaa","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a general knowledge question - I don't need to look at any files, I can answer from my knowledge.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about the migration steps.","outputTokens":361,"requestId":"67E9:247AEF:29A1F30:2DE53F4:69FD337D"},"id":"801468fe-7b73-4121-a57b-f73ca2f98d32","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:51:17.871Z","parentId":"746acc99-0989-4c49-95ba-149617f3306f"}
